com.teama.pds
Class ResourceList<T extends Resource>

java.lang.Object
  com.teama.pds.ResourceList<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
PeekResourceList
public class ResourceList<T extends Resource>
extends java.lang.Object

Author: Grant Kurtz Maintains a list of objects extending Resource, with a PriorityQueue as the backing data structure. The difference is this class only returns elements assuming that the resource itself is "available", whatever those conditions may be.

anyAvailable

public boolean anyAvailable()
Returns:
True if the first resource in the queue is available, otherwise false if there are no elements in the queue or the first resource isn't available.

checkAllInternalResources

public void checkAllInternalResources()
This method is necessary for cases where you have nested ResourceLists and it is necessary for each resource in the upper-level list to re-ask its top-most child if it is available. This is a must as the resources of the bottom-most resource may change availability while the top-most will not reflect this change (as it may be second in the queue and therefore never polled for available resources, and then subsequently the children are never re-polled for availability).
